tip.text: Lovely coffee shop hiding at hardware shop! Coffee was fantastic, and they serve beer too. Had Japanese Curry Bowl and Ethiopian manual brew. Perfect lazy weekends!

venue.name: Chye Seng Huat Hardware Coffee Bar

tip.text: The exhibitions are wonderful, combining both art and technology in friendly approach - some even suitable for kids. Some exhibitions are free and others charge entry fee.
There are beautiful places if you like gardens and flowers, such as the cloud forest and the flower dome. Spend the day there and you could watch the musical tree performance at the supertree grove.
Lovely cafe with some healthy home-made dishes!
The best place to be on top of the world! Must go.
Outpost on the hill for photograph session!
Nice not-so-rocky trail to with photo worthy lookout at the end
Lovely spot for brunch or lunch in the area. Delicious food, accompanied with great service from the floor. The place still uses old-time records!
Great neighborhood with huge park overlooking a pier and view to the City. Family friendly for sure!
The food here is delicious and definitely value for money! The tiny place is also well decorated. Great place for brunch.
Great pizza and chicken parma to share with friends. Large portion - beware!

contact.facebookName: Universal Italian Restaurant and Function Venue

tip.text: Nice rooftop bar with a view! And wide selection of drinks. Great to spend sunset. Come earlier for seats!
Practically nothing but a great view and the place for great photos!
Everything luxury you can ever find, and casino too! Otherwise you can also walk by the Yarra river or have some refreshing drinks by the river
Amazing exhibitions and lovely collection

formattedAddress: 328 Swanston St (btwn La Trobe St & Little Lonsdale St)
location.crossStreet: btwn La Trobe St & Little Lonsdale St

tip.text: Loved the special pork chop with broken rice. Go there slightly earlier or you may not get a table.
Comfortable room and nice breakfast! Good service too.

formattedAddress: Jalan Camplung Tanduk No 103 SP, Dhyana Pura
location.address: Jalan Camplung Tanduk No 103 SP, Dhyana Pura

tip.text: Delicious grills, especially the ribs, and wonderful Sundubu Chigae.
Nice place for brunch and to relax
If you like parks, come here
Great shopping center with easy parking, tall sky lights, and easy to navigate around the aisles.
Quick and efficient car wash!
Grilled Aji Aji fish is fantastic! Be aware, waiting time can be long.
They serve the best honey roasted cha shao in town! Also good for late night binging - serving porridge as well.

location.address: Ruko Grand Wijaya Center Blok C No. 4
formattedAddress: Ruko Grand Wijaya Center Blok C No. 4 (Jalan Dharmawangsa III)

tip.text: The most complete nasi campur you'll ever get in Jakarta. There's cha shao, shao rou, shao mai, satay, etc. Commonly served with a small bowl of clear soup.

formattedAddress: Grand Wijaya Center, Blok F no. 19 (Jln. Wijaya 2, Kebayoran)
location.address: Grand Wijaya Center, Blok F no. 19

tip.text: Go for the fried pork with sambal matah, with the pork skin fritters on the side. Simply delicious.
Wonderful room with perfect views all around the hotel. Buffet breakfast isn't tasting well, tho.

venue.name: Pan Pacific Nirwana Bali Resort, Tanah Lot

tip.text: Best place to go for company dinner. Pretty good service. VIP rooms are available. Better to reserve early.
The best place to find cheap and good local food!
Very good place. Large rooms, very good communal area, and definitely cozy.
You don't get to see sunset here, but you will definitely come back for the seafood dishes. Don't worry about ordering too many of the clams, they're cheap and are to die for. Don't miss the prawns!

formattedAddress: Jl. Four Seasons - Muaya Beach (Jl. Bukit Permai)

tip.text: The place to go for porridge in Bali. Best porridge with cakwe. Good for families/friends. The best hangover remedy too.
One of the best Medan style roasted pork dish in the city. Choose between mixed rice, or selection of meat to your hainam rice.

location.address: Taman Duta Mas Blok C1 B No. 6
formattedAddress: Taman Duta Mas Blok C1 B No. 6 (Jl. Pangeran Tubagus Angke, Jelambar)

venue.name: Nasi Gandul "Bu Endang" Khas Kota Pati

tip.text: The entry to all the galleries is $10 only.
The golden lava bun is a must try. However the other dishes are good too. Don't be surprised if the store persons aren't that polite to you, and better come early.

formattedAddress: Stall 10, Maxwell Food Centre (1 Kadayanallur St.)

venue.name: Tian Tian Hainanese Chicken Rice 天天海南鸡饭

formattedAddress: Stall 10, Maxwell Food Centre (1 Kadayanallur St.)

venue.name: Tian Tian Hainanese Chicken Rice 天天海南鸡饭

tip.text: The place to go for Ba Kut Teh. Be sure to have the pork knuckles too!

venue.name: Ng Ah Sio Pork Ribs Soup Eating House

tip.text: Great sop buntut at a homey kind of ambience. Loved it.
Cute furniture store with a collection of industrial furniture next to a cute café. They can make to order furnitures for you too, specializing on mahogany wood.
Very industrial ambience, yet relaxing. Do come before 4 to get seats easily. Coffee is good, and the all day brunch menu looks great.
Strategicly located hotel with great service. Rooms aren't too small. It's only a month old now, but it'll be one great hotel soon.
The food's pretty standard, but the place is good to spend one lazy Saturday with a view.
An outdoor and indoor art space. A place for inspiration, fun photo snapping, and to enjoy one lazy afternoon.
Probably the most authentic Sundanese cuisine I ever tasted. Very simple open-aired restaurant and truly affordable. Must try!
Their Sumatra blend is one special blend you won't find at other places. Must try. It is at the sampe place of Edelweiss hotel, make no mistake.
Good old fashioned food place. I prefer nasi bakmoy instead of nasi bakut. Interesting atmosphere. Located at a very small street, do allow yourself to walk. Parking may be difficult.
Heavenly croissants and coffee. Great way to spend lazy Saturdays.

formattedAddress: Pacific Place South Lobby (Jl. Jenderal Sudirman Kav. 52-53)

tip.text: Best brunch and coffee on Taman Ratu. Period.

formattedAddress: Jalan Taman Ratu Indah AA2 No. 33 (Jl. Surya Wijaya)
location.address: Jalan Taman Ratu Indah AA2 No. 33

tip.text: Fresh seafood! A little pricey but worth it!

formattedAddress: Lotte Shopping Avenue, 3rd Floor #09 & A02 (Jl. Prof. Dr. Satrio Kav. 3-5)

tip.text: Had the pork neck steak. Pretty decent 250g of grilled pork neck which was tender, but a little salty to my taste. The mashed potato was fine. Pretty good overall, with affordable pricing too.
Wonderful Fuqing dishes right here in Jakarta. Don't miss the special lemon chicken!

location.address: Rukan Garden House, Blok RGA 06-07, Pantai Indah Kapuk (PIK)
formattedAddress: Rukan Garden House, Blok RGA 06-07, Pantai Indah Kapuk (PIK)

tip.text: Great soto!
A little different taste than other Korean establishment. The Woo Samgyup is tasty!
Another time here. Must try the midnight espresso. Small but packs a flavorful punch than usual cup of espresso. Great pair of the sandwiches.
Was here for the blockbuster launch of Maybelline New York's White Super Fresh. Apparently the place can turn into a function place, not just for parties. I got outta there sober.
Best pork knuckle in town.

formattedAddress: Plaza Bisnis Kemang I, GF (Jalan Kemang Raya No. 2)

tip.text: The grilled chicken was pretty small in size, but tastes good! So was the tofu. Remember to wear pants, the mosquitos were quite a nuisance.
Pretty good la mian dishes, but the portions are pretty small.

formattedAddress: Lotte Shopping Avenue (Jl Prof Dr Satrio Kav 3-5)

tip.text: The orange beef and lemon chicken is a must try. Portions of the dishes are pretty small, it's okay to order more. Service is pretty good.

formattedAddress: Street Gallery Lt. 2, Pondok Indah Mall (Jalan Metro Pondok Indah)
location.address: Street Gallery Lt. 2, Pondok Indah Mall

tip.text: The kepiting soka is wonderfully crunchy, and the udang telor asin is tasty. Pretty good service too!

formattedAddress: Mal Metropolitan 2, Lantai 2 No. 1-3 (Jalan Kyai Haji Noer Ali)

tip.text: The Sego Ireng tastes good, a little salty, but still good. Had it with Wedang Oewoeh, really soothed my cold. Pretty cute place too!
Very good brunch place. Australian style. Food tasted great, and the place stirs conversation. Anyways, I felt like a tourist since everyone else is mostly caucasian.
Wonderful Sundanese commoner cuisine. Super tasty and very much affordable. The tables are looking the communal kind, easily sparking a conversation with others.

venue.name: Nasi Bancakan Mang Barna & Bi O'om

tip.text: The Vietnamese coffee is good. Loved it.

formattedAddress: Gandaria City, GF (Jalan Sultan Iskandar Muda)
Gandaria City, GF (Jalan Sultan Iskandar Muda)

tip.text: Always order the Jigoku Ramen if you like the heat. Great place for ramen with a punch, and a variety of condiments. The gyoza and karaage are also must try.
A high end italian restaurant. Loved the pizza, pasta, and escargot. Service was good too.

formattedAddress: Street Gallery 1st Floor (Jl. Metro Pondok Indah)

tip.text: You only need to order 2 things: (1) pork knuckle, (2) Paulaner lager.

formattedAddress: Grand Indonesia, East Mall, 2nd Floor (Jl. Mohammad Husni Thamrin No. 1)

tip.text: Definitely my family's favorite Korean BBQ place. Affordable yet tasteful. Best to have it with soju.
My friends' favorite place for seafood. Great tasteful and fresh seafood dishes. We usually order almost everything grilled on the menu, and wash it down with coconut water. Another carbo loading!
The best noodle place in Bogor. Best to go with family.
Lovely lovely pork dish! I always return here at every visit to Bali. Sometimes, I would take it back to Jakarta.
My favorite place with friends to have Korean chicken and ice cold beer all night long.

formattedAddress: Restaurant Arang 22, Lt. 2 (Jl. Tulodong Bawah No. 1A)

tip.text: Not as good as I initially thought, for the price. Would have been bigger or the flavor infused with the pannacotta itself.

formattedAddress: Pacific Place 4th Floor #63 (Jalan Jendral Sudirman Kavling 52-53)

tip.text: Creative dishes. Flavorful and creatively put together. A good place to spend some time with friends too.

formattedAddress: Gandaria City, Mainstreet GF (Jalan Sultan Iskandar Muda 5/8)

tip.text: One of the best ramen place I know. Very authentic Japanese noodles.

formattedAddress: Lotte Shopping Avenue,  2nd Floor #02A (Jalan Prof. Dr. Satrio Kav. 3-5)

tip.text: Surprisingly. This is also a great place to spend your lazy afternoon away and have coffee.

formattedAddress: Oakwood Premier Cosmo (Jl. Lingkar Mega Kuningan Lot. E4.2 No. 1)
location.crossStreet: Jl. Lingkar Mega Kuningan Lot. E4.2 No. 1

tip.text: Simple snacks the peranakan way is good, especially with hot coffee.
Happiness comes in a bowl of soup with rice on the side. Very much affordable and tasteful. My favorite is the one with 'telor muda.'
It is basically a foodcourt + leisure area + a mini market. I tried rabbit satays there. Pretty good. The place was overcrowded by lunchtime.
Another creative bar/pub, Mexican themed. Lovely Quessadias and Nachos. Perfect with drinks in the afternoon. Remember to snap around, the place is camera worthy.
After a good dip, snorkle, and sunbath by the beach, the 'catch of the day' is refreshing!
Legendary noodles. Sweet Mie Yamin Special is my pick. Definitely a destination every time I visit Bandung.
Crunchy fresh baguette, juicy tender beef slices with Vietnamese spices, crispy veggies. Wash down with the only drip coffee. Heaven... Nice outdoor place, too.
This place only accepts cash, but the porridge gets me return all the time. Opens 24/7. Do order extra cakwe on the side.
Get a full wash, the engine compartment and tire wax. It's worth it.
Creative coffee choices and interesting place. Too bad it is easily packed!

formattedAddress: Grand Indonesia Shopping Town, Pandawa Lobby
location.address: Grand Indonesia Shopping Town, Pandawa Lobby

tip.text: The desserts were pretty good. Spent the night chatting with friends over beer. Cute place, but a little too noisy for a good conversation.

formattedAddress: Senayan City Mall, LG Floor unit L-06B1
location.address: Senayan City Mall, LG Floor unit L-06B1

tip.text: Always loved the burgers. So far the Brie Burger and the Coffee Rub Burger are the best contenders. Anytime.

formattedAddress: Pondok Indah Mall 1, Lt. 3 (Jalan Metro Pondok Indah Blok 3B)

tip.text: Great cuts and grills at a little place on Seminyak. Must try the pork belly.
I love Korean wings.
I'm not a big fan of whisky, but this 'old fashioned' is certainly pretty good. I'm close to being a convert.

formattedAddress: Shangri-La Hotel, Level 1 (Jl. Jenderal Sudirman Kav. 1)

tip.text: Very rich broth! Great taste. Don't be discouraged with the oversupply of fats in the broth. Great ramen :)
Casual food. Great to spend time with friends over moscato. The mushroom soup is okay.
A very small place. Service wasn't right. We're asked to foot our bill due to a waiting queue when we were still in the middle of our conversation, when food took some time to be served.

location.address: St. Moritz Mall Puri Indah GF-98
formattedAddress: St. Moritz Mall Puri Indah GF-98

tip.text: Loved the fried kwetiau with mixed meat and tripes. Quite a big serving for a dish.
Strong flavors and definitely spicy! Loved the dishes. Pretty good service as well.

formattedAddress: Grand Indonesia Shopping Town, West Mall Level 5 (Jl. Mohammad Husni Thamrin No.1)
location.address: Grand Indonesia Shopping Town, West Mall Level 5

tip.text: Loved their crispy duck dish and the "sambal matah." Service is good and it doesn't take long for the food to be served. Can get pretty crowded at times, which brings down the Balinese experience.

formattedAddress: Cilandak Town Square, GF (Jalan TB Simatupang Kav. 17)

tip.text: Nice place for weekend brunch. Good food, and great environment for a good chat. The music is not very loud and the service is fine.

formattedAddress: The East Building, Lobby, GF (Jalan Lingkar Mega Kuningan Blok E3.2 No. 1)
location.crossStreet: Jalan Lingkar Mega Kuningan Blok E3.2 No. 1

tip.text: My family's favorite dim sum place. Pretty authentic taste and they've got discounts for eating in. Could be very crowded at times, but it isn't long waiting for a table. Improved service lately too.

formattedAddress: Lindeteves Trade Centre Lt. 6 (Jalan Hayam Wuruk No. 127)

venue.name: Sun City Restaurant and Luxury Club

tip.text: They offer great panadas!
Still finds the dishes better at the one in Melbourne. Pretty good all in all.

formattedAddress: Ruko Crown Golf Blok B No. 8-9, Pantai Indak Kapuk
location.address: Ruko Crown Golf Blok B No. 8-9, Pantai Indak Kapuk

tip.text: Essentially coffee bean with main dishes on the menu. The foods okay, but not excellent for the price.
Can't understand what is worth queueing for. The dessert is "Wow!" On the presentation side, but not on taste. Expensive, and crowded. Standard service.

location.address: Rukan Crown Golf Blok D No. 17 Bukit Golf Mediterania
formattedAddress: Rukan Crown Golf Blok D No. 17 Bukit Golf Mediterania

tip.text: Never failed to get myself a 'last sub' before my flight. Always know what you want out of the choices of meat, veggies, and condiments. The queue can take you at least 20 mins. Do come early.
My family's favorite Manadonese restaurant. Must try the grilled fish dishes, papaya flower, brennebon soup, and corn perkedel. Don't forget to try the es kacang for dessert.

formattedAddress: Jl. Panglima Polim V No. 15 (Kebayoran Baru)

tip.text: Juiciest & tastiest meatballs in the heart of the city. A must try!
Go for the paellas. The tapas can never go wrong too, and don't forget to get your Sangria Rosso refilled.

formattedAddress: Rukan Permata Senayan D25-26 (Jl. Tentara Pelajar)

tip.text: So far the best noodle place I've ever been to. Mixed pork (roasted and chasiu) karet noodle is my all time favorite. They serves the best fried meatballs too!

formattedAddress: Jl. Kembang Abadi VII Blok A No 12 No 22 (Puri Indah)
location.address: Jl. Kembang Abadi VII Blok A No 12 No 22

tip.text: Another good brunch place. Just for the noodle though, I'm not a fan of the fried meatballs.
Pretty good noodle dish with generous cuts of chicken on it. Not a big place, thus advisable to arrive slightly earlier than the lunch/dinner crowd.
Lovely Italian dishes to spoil your tastebuds. The place for family meals, or lunch after completing your 18th hole.

formattedAddress: Pondok Indah Golf Gallery (Jalan Metro Pondok Indah)

tip.text: The place for coffee and brunch menus. Laid back experience on weekends. Great for lazy Saturday mornings.

location.crossStreet: Jalan Kyai Haji Mas Mansyur No. 121
formattedAddress: Citywalk Sudirman, Level G (Jalan Kyai Haji Mas Mansyur No. 121)

tip.text: Authentic northern Chinese cuisine. Wonderful la mian noodles, attentive waitresses, happy tummy.
Highly premium cuts grilled into perfection. Romantic ambience perfect for a date night. Good service, too!

formattedAddress: Plaza Indonesia Lvl.1 #173 (Jalan MH Thamrin Kav. 28-30)

tip.text: Great all day breakfast, grills, apple crumble, and wine. Cozy, relaxed atmosphere. Good to dine with friends and family. Nice view towards HI roundabout too.

formattedAddress: Grand Indonesia East Mall Lt. 1 Unit 12 (Jalan Mohammad Husni Thamrin No. 1)
location.address: Grand Indonesia East Mall Lt. 1 Unit 12

tip.text: Loved the spare ribs. Tasty to the bones! Best to go with mashed potato on the side with a bottle of Bintang.

formattedAddress: Ruko Crown Golf Blok A55 (Jl. Marina Raya, Pantai Indah Kapuk)
location.crossStreet: Jl. Marina Raya, Pantai Indah Kapuk

tip.text: Great noodle brunch place. The fried meatballs & sweet potato balls are a must try. Don't be alarmed, here no receipt is given for your orders. Just pay, and ponder how much they cost on your own.
Very cozy and romantic atmosphere. The escargot was great! Was very much satisfied with my 8-hour lamb confit as well.
My wife loved the nougat ice cream more than the queue. Pretty good for IDR 20k! Just go for the ice cream, the other food like the satay or the rujak juhi is both pricey and taste borderline.

venue.name: Ragusa Es Italia Restaurant & Ice Cream

tip.text: Very nice, calming place. Great coffee. This place inspires creativity.
Try the Bistik Sapi, Fuyunghai, Daging Kuluyuk, Cumi Goreng Mentega, Lumpia Udang, and Es Teler. Portions are generous, beware when ordering.
Try the beef hobatayaki or the black cod teriyaki. All meats served super fresh, cooked to perfection. Highly recommended. Reservation is a must.
The street food served here is like those served at any other place. However, you could get quite a view of the sun setting behind tall buildings in front of you while having your meal.
Pretty tasty Chinese food. The cereal chicken we had was a hit. The place was crowded the whole time. Recommended.
